     <-----<----- Player Owned Establishments ----->----->
     
Congratulations! You are an establishment owner on DarkWind! You are
now part of the player driven economy. 

What's changed? --> Establishments are no longer ash based. What this
means is that all meal, keg, drink, snack, etc cost are solely based
on an amount PER HP/SP. That means that all lvl 10 meals of 100/100
will cost the same amount regardless of ash level. 

For you, this means that your MARGINS (the amount you make from each
sale) will be the sole way you make money. No more inflated costs of 
buying ash,etc. This also means that the establishment system will be 
more competitive.

Player owned establishments are only able to create items LEVEL 6 and
above. Newbies will be taken care of by the new Newbie Inn and Pub!

Also, you will notice that the maximum amount for healing has increased.
The amount that can be eaten/drank has not changed, but the healing
availability has. Word of caution, just because it can go to X amount
doesn't always mean it should. Things get VERY expensive the higher 
they heal.

In your establishment, there is a command "owners", it lists all
the various commands you have available as an establishment owner on 
DarkWind.

As a reminder, inactivity of 6 months or longer will forfeit your
establishment. This does NOT mean you have to log in as the the owner
though. If you only play a secondary character, I'm smart enough to 
recognize that you're still active.
